<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-06-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1447.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-06-10"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 10, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            despatch of the 25th ultimo, (No. 969.) The information you convey to
                            this department in regard to the arrangements which were provided by the
                            British authorities for the apprehension of the assassin Booth, in the
                            event of his reaching her Majesty’s dominions, is received with much
                            satisfaction.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of
                                    State.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>